al. Abolition feminism reveals the possibility of a just world beyond the carceral state, which is fundamentally unable to respond to, let alone remedy, harm. As Imperfect Victims shows, abolition feminism is the only politics and practice that can undo the indescribable damage inflicted on survivors by the very system purporting to protect them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAbused womenxLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aAbused womenxLegal status, laws, etc. 0aFeminism2DLC. 0aFeminism. 0aIntimate partner violencezUnited States2DLC. 0aIntimate partner violencezUnited States. 0aPrison abolition movementszUnited States2DLC. 0aPrison abolition movementszUnited States. 0aVictims of family violencexLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aVictims of family violencexLegal status, laws, etc. 0aWomen prisonersxCrimes against2DLC. 0aWomen prisonersxCrimes against. 0aWomen prisonersxLegal status, laws, etc2DLC. 0aWomen prisonersxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh  aPOC.  aabolition.  aafrican american.  acriminal legal system.  acriminalization.  adomestic violence.  aequality.  agender nonconforming.  ainequality.  ainequity.  ainjustice.  ainstitutions.  alaw.  alegal.  aminority.  aprosecution.  asexism.  asurvivor.  asystems.  atrans.  aunfairness.  awomen of color.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520391130?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520391130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520391130/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles